"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-usc-trojan-news-usc-trojans-alum-lands-silver-medal-in-hurdles-at-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Team USA continues to win medals at the 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 60, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9899845093322555, \"rank\": 0.01009840563358391, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time, it's on the track with renowned hurdler and former USC Trojan Anna Cockrell.\", \"from\": 61, \"to\": 148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 123, \"end\": 126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 0.9999999930173544, \"rank\": 6.420839156505612e-09, \"text\": \"USC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\"}, {\"begin\": 134, \"end\": 147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Cockrell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cockrell represented the United States in the 400m hurdle, earning the silver medal for a personal best time of 51.87 seconds.\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9938977665878731, \"rank\": 0.005659096376544267, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished shortly behind Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, also from the United States, who set a world record at 50.37 seconds.\", \"from\": 277, \"to\": 401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998869229849, \"rank\": 8.147582623403856e-08, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9938977665878731, \"rank\": 0.005659096376544267, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USC alum@AnnaCockrell48wins SILVER in the#Paris2024400m hurdles with a PR of 51.87!\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 403, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 0.9999999930173544, \"rank\": 6.420839156505612e-09, \"text\": \"USC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u0088\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ba\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b8#USC2Paris|#OlympiansMadeHerepic.twitter.com/702O4PP5zf  Cockrell previously qualified for the 2020Summer Olympicsin Tokyo.\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She made it to the final race but was disqualified after officials discovered that she had made a lane violation.\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This time around I was almost more nervous at the Olympic Trials than I was in 2021,\\\" Cockrell told WCNC Charlotte.\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Motor_Speedway\", \"score\": 0.9758057724951665, \"rank\": 0.01831277308517706, \"text\": \"Charlotte\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Motor_Speedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Motor_Speedway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I felt in 2021 I was able to sneak my way onto the team, where this time people know my name and what I am able to run.\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was almost more of a relief to make the team this time.\\\"\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 1035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cockrell is an advocate for the mental health of student-athletes, which she addressed in her commencement speech at USC.\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 0.9999999930173544, \"rank\": 6.420839156505612e-09, \"text\": \"USC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe two things I do not like to talk about are the fact that I have battled depression on and off since my 10th-grade year and that I am a perfectionist,\\\" Cockrell said.\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This perfectionism means that I do not like to ask for help I do not like to seem weak, I do not like to let people know that I struggle.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Cockrell's track and field career began in high school, first earning gold at the 2015 Pan American U20 Championships.\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1563, \"end\": 1593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_Pan_American_U20_Athletics_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pan American U20 Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_Pan_American_U20_Athletics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_Pan_American_U20_Athletics_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She would then participate in the World U20 Championships, where she would again in the 400m hurdles as well as the 4x400m relay.\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 1724, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterward, Cockrell would attend USC.\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1759, \"end\": 1762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 0.9999999930173544, \"rank\": 6.420839156505612e-09, \"text\": \"USC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2019, she became the NCAA champion for the 400m hurdle with a time of 55.23.\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1788, \"end\": 1801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Men's_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championship\", \"score\": 0.6690125941787848, \"rank\": 0.4947401718609462, \"text\": \"NCAA champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Men's_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Men's_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championship\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later that year, she won the silver medal in hurdles and gold in relay at the Pan American Games in Lima.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"score\": 0.9853316084811915, \"rank\": 0.014841426339737425, \"text\": \"Pan American Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1944, \"end\": 1948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lima_District\", \"score\": 0.9994042779985165, \"rank\": 0.00042138659835786537, \"text\": \"Lima\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lima_District\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lima_District\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After all events were canceled in 2020 due to the COVID-19 Pandemic, Cockrell truly made a name for herself in 2021.\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 2067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After being named 2021 Pac-12 Women's Track & Field Scholar Athlete of the Year, Cockrell led the Trojans to their third consecutive conference team title at the Pac-12 championships.\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2167, \"end\": 2174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 0.9999999997319264, \"rank\": 2.658102503573048e-10, \"text\": \"Trojans\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She then became the 2021 NCAA champion for the women's 100m hurdle and 400m hurdle, helping USC win the team title at the 2021 NCAA Division I Outdoor Track and Field Championships and becoming the second woman in history to win both events at the NCAA championships.\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2273, \"end\": 2291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2021_NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2021 NCAA champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2021_NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2021_NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 2345, \"end\": 2348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 0.9999999930173544, \"rank\": 6.420839156505612e-09, \"text\": \"USC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", 